    "For example, Song and Guan (2022) emphasize that local support, such as school resources and community engagement, plays a crucial role in shaping teachers' interdisciplinary competencies.",
    "Additionally, regional differences, as observed in studies by Dong (2016) and Zeng et al. (2024), illustrate that geographic location and local education policies can significantly affect the outcomes of PD programs.",
    "These findings demonstrate that while various PD approaches, such as interdisciplinary training, reflective practices, and technology integration, have positively influenced STEM teaching in China, the effectiveness of these initiatives is also shaped by multiple factors, including regional contexts, teacher experience, and institutional support.",
    "These insights can guide future PD programs better to address the diverse needs of STEM educators in China and foster a more robust and adaptable teaching workforce.",
    "Influence of Teacher Efficacy and Regional Differences."
